txt.en: You defeated many Warg-riders within the Floodwells.
Warg-riders are a dangerous threat to the people who live within the Floodfells, and those who must adventure there.

Warg-riders prowl the hills and valleys of the Floodfells, searching for easy prey and serving as the eyes of their dark masters in Gundabad. They must be defeated before they are able to return to the mountains with report of your movements along the Langflood.
Warg-riders are on the loose throughout the Floodfells, searching for easy prey.
Warg-riders from Gundabad threaten the peace and safety of those who live within the Floodfells.

The Warg-riders you defeated will not return to Gundabad with report of your movements. That silence may also speak volumes to their dark masters, but that is a risk you have chosen to take. The folk who do live in the Floodfells will be safer for your efforts.
